                        <div class="page-header">
                            <h2>
                                Method Statements and Risk Assessments
                            </h2>


                        </div>






                        <div itemprop="articleBody">
                            <p>The software contains method statements for each energy efficiency measure,&nbsp; default risk assessments and Toolbox Talks within a powerful database, these can be easily duplicated, the assessment automatically includes all of the relevant project details. Each risk assessment can be customised where specific hazards are present in a project. The built-in PDF printer and contact list allows you to issue copies of the risk assessments individually to all relevant parties via e-mail with the correct information inserted into the assessment.</p>
<h4>Key Benefits</h4>
<ul class="bullet1">
<li>
<p>Automatically produce method statements, risk assessment templates and toolbox talks with buit-in mailmerge information of project details</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Database system not MS Word documnents, you can duplicate and create your own templates. See the tutorials to find out how simple it is.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>PDF Printer and email interface. No need for Adobe Acrobat.Issue assessments to multiple users via e-mail using a distribution list</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save PDF versions of the issued documents to your computer. No need for confusing system managing file names of various documents.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Database includes contact list to insert information into the templates Incorporate your logo and signature automatically in the documents</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4>Method Statements</h4>
<p>A method statement is available for each green deal energy efficiency measure. For example if you are carrying out loft and cavity wall insulation you will include two method statements within the project and the customer's details are automatically inserted into the method statements.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<table style="width: 90%;" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td valign="top">
<h4>Heating, ventilation and air conditioning</h4>
